race.description: Kevlacat Power Boats Australia Maiden Handicap
race.comment: HIT THE SWITCH (5) is unlucky to still be a maiden hitting the top-four in all three outings to date and strikes a very winnable contest here. Strips fitter second-up and should be going very close to breaking the maiden status. KOHLER KID (1) is first-up here but showed enough in his first preparation to warrant consideration in a race like this. Expected to run well while fresh. ENTERPRISE KHAN (8) has been thereabouts in both career efforts and looks a top-three hope despite the wide draw. KUIA MA (6) just missed the frame here when facing the starter for the first time and will have derived benefit from that day at the races. In the mix. HARRYTHEWIZ (9) is drawn to get all the favours from the inside marble and must be respected from the Maher yard. Include in calculations.
